The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:14 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index fell 0.2 percent to 22,518.45. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index dropped 0.2 percent to 3,071.45.  Copper miners dropped on early losses in the metal in New
York.    Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, slid 1.9 percent to $2.05. Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde
SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc.,
fell for a fourth session, dropping 1 percent to $47.50.  Gold miners slumped after futures fell from a record in New
York.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the countryâ€™s
biggest precious-metals miner, fell 2.4 percent to $44.50. Gold
Fields La Cima SA (LACIMAC1 PE), a unit of Gold Fields Ltd.,
dropped 1.2 percent to 3.42 soles.    Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, rose 1.9 percent to $1.06
after natural gas advanced for a third day in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:  Alex Emery  in Lima at 
